{
  "texts": [
    "One major concern is the privacy and security of patient data.",
    "NLP systems rely on large amounts of data, including sensitive patient information, to perform tasks effectively.",
    "Ensuring that these data are stored and processed in a HIPAA-secured manner is essential to protect patient confidentiality.Another challenge is the potential for bias, a well-known limitation of LLMs.",
    "If the data used to train NLP models are not diverse or representative, the algorithms may produce biased or inaccurate results.",
    "This could lead to disparities in patient care, particularly for patients from underrepresented groups."
  ]
}